spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_PROTOCOL_SELECTION
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the type of protocol. BFM supposrts AXI4, AXI3, AXI-S and AXI4 Lite.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_MODE_SELECT
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select whether the BFM should be a master or slave.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXI3_ID_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the ID width.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXI3_DATA_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the Data width.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_INTERCONNECT_M_AXI3_READ_ISSUING
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This defines the maximum number of outstanding transactions. Any attempt to generate more traffic while this limit has been reached will be handled by stalling until at least one of the outstanding transactions has finished.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXI3_EXCLUSIVE_ACCESS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter informs the master that exclusive access is supported by the slave. A value of 1 means it is supported so the response check will expect an EXOKAY, or else give a warning, in response to an exclusive access. A value of 0 means the slave does not support this so a response of OKAY will be expected in response to an exclusive access.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI3_DATA_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Data bus can be 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256, 512 or 1024 bits wide

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI3_ID_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the ID width.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI3_MEMORY_MODEL_MODE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The parameter puts the slave BFM into a simple memory model mode. This means that the slave BFM will automatically respond to all transfers and will not require any of the API functions to be called by the test

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_INTERCONNECT_S_AXI3_READ_ACCEPTANCE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This defines the maximum number of outstanding transactions. Any attempt to generate more traffic while this limit has been reached will be handled by stalling until at least one of the outstanding transactions has finished.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI3_BASEADDR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter specified the base address. This has to be specified as in 0x format

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI3_HIGHADDR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter specified the high address. This has to be specified as in 0x format

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI3_EXCLUSIVE_ACCESS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter informs the slave that exclusive access is supported. A value of 1 means it is supported so the automatic generated response will be an EXOKAY to exclusive accesses. A value of 0 means the slave does not support this so a response of OKAY will be automatically generated in response to exclusive accesses.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXIS_TID_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the TID width.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXIS_TDATA_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Data bus can be in the range of 8 to 1024, in multiples of 8

spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the TDEST width.

spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the TUSER width.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXIS_MAX_PACKET_SIZE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The value must be specified as an integer multiple of the DATA_BUS_WIDTH. For example; If DATA_BUS_WIDTH = 32 bits and MAX_PACKET_SIZE = 2 then the maximum packet size is 64 bits.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXIS_MAX_OUTSTANDING_TRANSACTIONS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This defines the maximum number of outstanding transactions. Any attempt to generate more traffic while this limit has been reached will be handled by stalling until at least one of the outstanding transactions has finished

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXIS_STROBE_NOT_USED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Default is 0 i.e. Strobe Checks enabled. Changing this to 1 i.e. disabled, will only disable the associated checks.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXIS_KEEP_NOT_USED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Default is 0 i.e. Keep Checks enabled. Changing this to 1 i.e. disabled, will only disable the associated checks.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXIS_STROBE_SIG_NOT_USED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Setting this to 1 will disable the ports associated with TSTRB.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXIS_KEEP_SIG_NOT_USED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Setting this to 1 will disable the ports associated with TKEEP.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_TID_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the TID width.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_TDATA_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Data bus can be in the range of 8 to 1024, in multiples of 8

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_TUSER_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the TUSER width.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_TDEST_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the TDEST width.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_MAX_PACKET_SIZE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The value must be specified as an integer multiple of the DATA_BUS_WIDTH. For example; If DATA_BUS_WIDTH = 32 bits and MAX_PACKET_SIZE = 2 then the maximum packet size is 64 bits.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_MAX_OUTSTANDING_TRANSACTIONS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This defines the maximum number of outstanding transactions. Any attempt to generate more traffic while this limit has been reached will be handled by stalling until at least one of the outstanding transactions has finished.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_STROBE_NOT_USED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Setting this to 1 will disable the checks associated with TSTRB. This does not disable the ports.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_KEEP_NOT_USED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Setting this to 1 will disable the checks associated with TKEEP. This does not disable the ports.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_STROBE_SIG_NOT_USED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Setting this to 1 will disable the ports associated with TSTRB.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXIS_KEEP_SIG_NOT_USED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Setting this to 1 will disable the ports associated with TKEEP.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_NARROW_BURST
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Selecting this sets an attribute on the AXI interface. Select this when the connected IP supports narrow bursts. When not selected ensure that BFM does not issue any narrow bursts.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_NARROW_BURST_SLAVE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Selecting this sets an attribute on the AXI interface. Select this when the connected IP supports narrow bursts. When not selected ensure that BFM does not issue any narrow bursts.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_NARROW_BURST_AXI3
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Selecting this sets an attribute on the AXI interface. Select this when the connected IP supports narrow bursts. When not selected ensure that BFM does not issue any narrow bursts.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_NARROW_BURST_SLAVE_AXI3
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Selecting this sets an attribute on the AXI interface. Select this when the connected IP supports narrow bursts. When not selected ensure that BFM does not issue any narrow bursts.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_WRITE_BURST_TRANSFER_DATA_GAP
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: It controls the gap between the write data transfers that comprise a write data burst. It is measured in clock cycles. It can be changed during runtime using set_write_burst_data_transfer_gap API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_RESPONSE_TIMEOUT
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: It determines when the task that is waiting for a response should timeout. It is measured in clock cycles. It can be changed during runtime using set_response_timeout API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_DISABLE_RESET_VALUE_CHECKS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter disables the check for the reset value of input signals to the BFM. It can be changed during runtime using set_disable_reset_value_checks API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_WRITE_ID_ORDER_CHECK_FEATURE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter enables the write ID ordering checks which may be required for error testing. It can be changed during runtime using set_write_id_order_check_feature_value API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_CLEAR_SIGNALS_AFTER_HANDSHAKE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter enables or disables the setting of BFM output signals to reset values between transfers. It can be changed during runtime using set_clear_signals_after_handshake API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_ERROR_ON_SLVERR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter enables or disables errors on SLVERR responses to reads and writes. It can be changed during runtime using set_error_on_slverr API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_ERROR_ON_DECERR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter enables or disables errors on DECERR responses to reads and writes. It can be changed during runtime using set_error_on_decerr API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_STOP_ON_ERROR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter enables or disables the stopping of the simulation on an error condition. It can be changed during runtime using set_stop_on_error API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_CHANNEL_LEVEL_INFO
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter controls the printing of channel level information messages. It can be changed during runtime using set_channel_level_info API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_FUNCTION_LEVEL_INFO
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter controls the printing of function level information messages. It can be changed during runtime using set_function_level_info API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_READ_BURST_DATA_TRANSFER_GAP
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: It controls the gap between the read data transfers that comprise a read data burst. It is measured in clock cycles. It can be changed during runtime using set_read_burst_data_transfer_gap API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_WRITE_RESPONSE_GAP
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: It controls the gap between the reception of the last write transfer and the write response. It is measured in clock cycles. It can be changed during runtime using set_write_response_gap API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_READ_RESPONSE_GAP
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: It controls the gap between the reception of the read address transfer and the start of first read data transfer. It is measured in clock cycles. It can be changed during runtime using set_read_response_gap API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_WRITE_BURST_ADDRESS_DATA_PHASE_GAP
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Write Burst Address Data Phase Gap
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: It controls the gap between the write address phase and the write data burst inside the WRITE_BURST task. It is measured in clock cycles. It can be changed during runtime using set_write_burst_address_data_phase_gap API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_WRITE_BURST_DATA_ADDRESS_PHASE_GAP
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Write Burst Data Address Phase Gap
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: It controls the gap between the write data burst and the write address phase inside the WRITE_BURST_CONCURRENT. It is measured in clock cycles. It can be changed during runtime using set_write_burst_data_address_phase_gap API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_PACKET_TRANSFER_GAP
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: It controls the gap between the transfers in a packet. It is measured in clock cycles.It can be changed during runtime using set_packet_transfer_gap API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_INPUT_SIGNAL_DELAY
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This is used to move the BFM input signals off the simulation clock edge if needed. It can be changed during runtime using set_input_signal_delay API.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_TASK_RESET_HANDLING
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This determines BFM behaviour during RESET. It can be changed during runtime using set_task_call_and_reset_handling API.
